Date: Tue 5 Oct 2021
Source: G1 [machine transl, edited]
https://g1.globo.com/ac/acre/noticia/2021/10/05/acre-monta-sala-de-situacao-para-monitorar-surto-de-diarreia-ha-quase-20-mil-casos-confirmados.ghtml


Acre sets up a situation room to monitor an outbreak of diarrhea; almost 20 000 cases confirmed
---------------------------------------------------------------
Of the 22 municipalities in Acre, 11 are on high alert. Cities with the highest number of registered cases are Cruzeiro do Sul and Tarauaca, according to the Center for Water and Food Transmission Diseases (NDTHA) of the Health Department of Acre (Sesacre). The State Department of Health (Sesacre) set up a situation room to monitor the nearly 20 000 cases of diarrhea registered in the state. A health team is in the Jurua region to assess the significant increase in cases, mainly in the municipalities of Cruzeiro do Sul, Mancio Lima and Rodrigues Alves.

According to the latest survey, carried out in epidemiological week 38 (considering the period 3 Jan 2021 to 25 Sep 2021), there [have been] more than 19 900 people with the disease. In all, 11 cities are on high alert because of the increase in cases. The data are from the Center for Water and Food Transmission Diseases (NDTHA) of Sesacre, which indicate in the same period of 2020, 13 500 cases were registered. The Sesacre Health Surveillance Department informed that a survey is being carried out on the possible causes of the increase in cases.

Surveillance actions in health, primary and primary care, medical and laboratory assistance are already being carried out in the last 10 epidemiological weeks to discover the causes of the disease outbreak. According to the data, cases began to increase in the state from 25 Jul 2021, which corresponds to epidemiological week 30. According to the latest bulletin, of the 22 municipalities, 11 are on high alert. They are: Assis Brasil, Capixaba, Cruzeiro do Sul, Epitaciolandia, Feijo, Jordao, Marshal Thaumaturgo, Rodrigues Alves, Santa Rosa, Senator Guiomard and Tarauaca.

The cities with the highest number of registered cases in week 38 were Cruzeiro do Sul, with 141 and Tarauaca, with 78.

The head of the Health Surveillance Department at Sesacre, Gabriel Mesquita, said that they were alerted by the Center for Diseases and Water and Food Transmission in the 30th epidemiological week and, since then, they have worked with the municipalities, in order to contribute to the construction strategies to minimize the impact of this outbreak on the population. "The actions are carried out by the municipalities and the secretariat continues to support the issue of the viability of those they are going to take. Action is up to them and we provide support," he pointed out.

The cities that are on alert are: Acrelandia (25), Brasileia (29), Mancio Lima (19), Rio Branco (419) and Sena Madureira (50). But Bujari, Manoel Urbano, Placido de Castro, Porto Acre [did not provide data], Porto Walter and Xapuri are instructed to investigate if there is underreporting.

[byline: Janine Brasil]

